[0m[1G[0m[0m[?25h{"verdict": "pass", "rationale": "Recipe 7.10 demonstrates strong clinical accuracy (correctly frames the timing problem in population health, appropriately distinguishes static risk from dynamic hazard trajectories, and acknowledges the counterfactual/causal inference challenge), sound architecture (event-driven pipeline with batch and real-time paths using appropriate AWS services under BAA with KMS encryption, VPC isolation, and CloudTrail auditing), and adequate security posture (HIPAA-compliant service selection, encryption at rest and in transit, IAM least-privilege enumerated). Prioritized findings: HIGH — The recipe does not address the ethical/IRB implications of the recommended holdout strategy (withholding intervention from flagged patients to preserve training signal), which could violate institutional review requirements and patient safety obligations; remediation: add explicit guidance on equipoise-based randomization, IRB approval requirements, and safety monitoring boards. HIGH — No model fairness or bias audit is described despite known disparities in healthcare data density across demographics; remediation: add a fairness evaluation section covering subgroup calibration (race, age, SES) and disparate impact testing before deployment. MEDIUM — The architecture lacks a human-in-the-loop override or escalation path when the model produces clinically implausible recommendations (e.g., suppressing outreach for a clearly deteriorating patient due to fatigue dampening); remediation: add clinical override mechanisms and alerting for edge cases. MEDIUM — No mention of model monitoring for distribution shift or concept drift in the production scoring path beyond CloudWatch latency metrics; remediation: integrate SageMaker Model Monitor with data quality and prediction drift detection, with automated alerting and retraining triggers. LOW — The cost estimate range is broad ($2,500–$8,000/month) without guidance on what drives costs to the high end or how to optimize; remediation: add a cost optimization section with instance right-sizing and auto-scaling recommendations. LOW — Related recipes reference Chapter 15 (RL) which may not yet exist; remediation: verify cross-references resolve or add a note that the chapter is forthcoming."}